========= * Steps to connect to GCP instance from Mac * =========

After creating VM instance from the GCP console, please follow below steps.

1.Install Gcloud CLI - https://docs.cloud.google.com/sdk/docs/install-sdk using this link you can follow steps to install Gcloud into your mac

if any error like - "zsh gcloud not found" then add the gcloud instaled directly to zsh with below two commands example.

  source /Users/khajasaifanmulla/downloads/google-cloud-sdk/path.zsh.inc   
  source /Users/khajasaifanmulla/downloads/google-cloud-sdk/completion.zsh.inc

Now you can able to run gcloud commands.

2. to connect to VM machine use below command.

    gcloud compute ssh VM_NAME --project=PROJECT_ID --zone=ZONE

  ex: gcloud compute ssh instance-20251112-060038 --natural-oxygen-473509-p2 --zone=us-central1-a

  ==> make sure to create project and note down project id and connect. even if it ask for "Generating public/private rsa key pair", please create it and run the command again.
